1. Purpose and Summary.
   This License is designed for software where the licensor wishes to allow use, copying, execution, and limited redistribution of unmodified code for non-commercial purposes, while prohibiting distribution of modifications and commercial use. It is inspired by Creative Commons BY-NC-ND 4.0 but adapted for software. It is not an official Creative Commons license and is not “open source” as defined by the Open Source Initiative.

2. Definitions.
   2.1 “Licensed Software” means the software made available by Licensor under this License, including source code (“Source Code”) and compiled forms (“Object Code”), and any associated documentation.
   2.2 “You” (or “Your”) means any individual or entity exercising permissions under this License.
   2.3 “Non-Commercial Use” means any use that is not intended for or directed toward commercial advantage or monetary compensation. Non-Commercial Use includes personal use, academic research and teaching, evaluation, and internal experimentation not deployed in production to deliver services to third parties. Non-Commercial Use excludes (a) offering, providing, or enhancing a product or service for a fee; (b) use in production systems that support a business function; (c) software-as-a-service (SaaS), platform-as-a-service (PaaS), or similar hosted offerings; (d) use by or for a commercial entity where the primary purpose is operational use rather than evaluation.
   2.4 “Derivative Work” means any work that is based on or incorporates the Licensed Software or any portion of it with modifications, translations, or other changes such that it is an adaptation under applicable copyright law.
   2.5 “Larger Work” means a work that combines the Licensed Software in unmodified form with other separate and independent works, such as by aggregation, dynamic or static linking, or packaging.
   2.6 “Contribution” means any original work of authorship, including modifications to the Licensed Software, submitted intentionally to the Licensor for inclusion in the project.
   2.7 “Contributor” means the Licensor and any individual or entity that submits a Contribution.
   2.8 “Patent Claims” means all patent claims, including claims of continuation, continuation-in-part, and reissue, that a Contributor can license and that are necessarily infringed by their Contribution alone or by combination of their Contribution with the Licensed Software.

3. Grant of Copyright License.
   Subject to Section 5 (Restrictions) and Your compliance with this License, Licensor grants You a worldwide, royalty-free, non-sublicensable, non-exclusive, irrevocable (except as stated in Section 9) license to:
   3.1 use, reproduce, and execute the Licensed Software for Non-Commercial Use;
   3.2 make and keep private technical modifications that are strictly necessary to compile, configure, or integrate the Licensed Software (e.g., build scripts, dependency pins, path adjustments) (“Technical Modifications”), provided that You do not distribute the Licensed Software in modified form;
   3.3 create Larger Works and (for Non-Commercial Use) distribute Object Code of the Larger Work that includes the Licensed Software unmodified, provided that (a) the Licensed Software’s Source Code is included unmodified or made available via a URL that is publicly accessible at no charge, (b) You preserve the notices required by Section 4, and (c) recipients are able to extract and use the Licensed Software as a separate component under this License.

4. Attribution and Notices.
   Any distribution permitted under this License must, in a reasonable manner customary for software, include: (a) the above copyright notice; (b) this License text; (c) a notice identifying the Licensed Software and original authors; and (d) a copy of, or link to, the original repository or homepage if provided by Licensor. If the Licensed Software is used in a user-facing Larger Work, reasonable attribution in documentation, “About” screens, or help text satisfies this requirement.

5. Restrictions (No Derivatives; Non-Commercial; No Additional Terms).
   5.1 No Distribution of Modified Code. You may not distribute the Licensed Software in modified form, including patches, forks, translations, re-implementations, or feature-altered builds. All public redistribution must contain the Licensed Software unmodified.
   5.2 Non-Commercial Only. You may not use the Licensed Software for commercial purposes, including but not limited to providing hosted services, operating production workloads for or within a business, or generating revenue or other commercial advantage.
   5.3 No Additional Restrictions. You may not impose terms or technological measures on the Licensed Software that legally or practically restrict recipients from exercising the permissions granted by this License. Distribution via platforms that apply technical protection measures (e.g., app stores) is permitted only if You also make available to the same recipients, at no charge, an unprotected copy of the Licensed Software (and any required build/installation instructions) under this License.
   5.4 No Trademark License. This License does not grant rights to use Licensor’s or Contributors’ names, logos, or trademarks.

6. Patent License.
   Each Contributor grants You a perpetual, worldwide, royalty-free, non-exclusive, irrevocable (except as stated in Section 9) patent license to make, have made, use, offer to sell, sell, import, and otherwise run, for Non-Commercial Use permitted here, the Licensed Software, solely to the extent that their Contribution or their Contribution’s combination with the Licensed Software, in the form distributed by the Licensor, infringes the Contributor’s Patent Claims.

7. Patent Retaliation.
   If You or Your affiliate institute patent litigation (including a cross-claim or counterclaim in a lawsuit) alleging that the Licensed Software or a Contribution infringes a Patent Claim, then any licenses granted to You under this License automatically terminate as of the date such litigation is filed.

8. Contributions Back to the Project.
   Unless You enter into a separate agreement with Licensor, any Contribution You submit is licensed by You to Licensor under this same License, with the patent license in Section 6. You represent that You have the right to grant such licenses and that Your Contribution is an original work by You.

9. Term and Termination.
   This License takes effect upon Your acceptance and continues unless terminated. Your rights under this License automatically terminate if You materially breach it and fail to cure within 30 days of becoming aware of the breach. Termination under Section 7 is immediate and without cure. Upon termination, You must cease exercise of the rights granted by this License; however, recipients who received the Licensed Software from You under this License will not have their licenses terminated, provided they remain in compliance. Provisions that by their nature should survive termination do so, including Sections 6–13.

10. Source Availability for Redistributed Binaries.
    If You distribute an Object Code Larger Work that includes the Licensed Software, You must provide access to the exact, unmodified Source Code of the Licensed Software used to build that Object Code, via a durable public URL or as a bundle accompanying the Object Code, for as long as You distribute the Object Code.

